+# Envelope Laws
+
+This directory contains operator-facing documentation for the envelope-law layer
+of MFCS–OMEGA.
+
+## Purpose
+
+Envelope laws define the admissible region of system evolution. They are global
+constraints over traces, state depth, and admissible inputs. They are not the
+dynamics themselves; they are the budget, boundary, and admissibility surface
+that the dynamics must respect.
+
+## Primary artifacts
+
+- `phi-A.md` — law note for the φ-governed attractor family.
+- `spec/modules/EnvelopeLaws.tla` — canonical envelope-law module.
+- `spec/modules/envelope-laws.tla` — compatibility layer with backward-compatible
+  aliases and legacy names.
+
+## Core predicates
+
+The compatibility module exposes the following predicates:
+
+- `DepthBound`
+- `InputBound`
+- `HistoryFinite`
+- `EnvelopeBudget`
+- `InEnvelope`
+
+These are intended to be read and reused by operators, reviewers, and legacy
+spec references.
+
+## Reproducibility path
+
+To rebuild the mirror with envelope-law metadata surfaced:
+
+```bash
+./tools/run-all.sh
+```
+
+This runs verification, mirror generation, and packaging, keeping the operator
+workflow and mirror artifact aligned.
